{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/setup-jekyll-blog-with-netlify/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"e01c4647-6bba-5d55-9f07-e3eeebf1773d","parent":{"relativePath":"blog/2018-01-31-setup-jekyll-blog-with-netlify.md"},"fields":{"slug":"/setup-jekyll-blog-with-netlify/"},"html":"<p>As I'm not (yet) very experienced with web developing this guide can be obvious. However, it's worth noted (at least for me) so I can check it if I have to go through the setup process again.</p>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-setup-jekyll-blog\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#how-to-setup-jekyll-blog\" aria-label=\"how to setup jekyll blog permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How to setup Jekyll blog</h2>\n<p>I decided to try setting up blog using Jekyll. As a base of it I used <a href=\"https://github.com/barryclark/jekyll-now\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">jekyll-now</a> repo.</p>\n<h3 id=\"github-pages\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#github-pages\" aria-label=\"github pages permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>GitHub Pages</h3>\n<p>For running it on GitHub Pages it was pretty easy, as written in the documentation. Just fork, rename repo to yourusername.github.io, wait up to 10 mins and you're all set. <del>However, as GitHub Pages don't support (and as far as I know don't plan to) HTTPS for custom domains</del> I tried to use <a href=\"https://netlify.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Netlify</a> as another platform to host it. </p>\n<p><strong>Update 2018-05-01</strong>: the above statement about GH Pages not supporting custom domains SSL is no longer valid as per <a href=\"https://blog.github.com/2018-05-01-github-pages-custom-domains-https/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">that announcement</a>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"netlify\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#netlify\" aria-label=\"netlify permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Netlify</h3>\n<p>One of the services that supports HTTPS for custom domains is <a href=\"https://netlify.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Netlify</a>. I quickly found <a href=\"https://www.netlify.com/blog/2015/10/28/a-step-by-step-guide-jekyll-3.0-on-netlify/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">this instruction</a>.</p>\n<p>However, it turned out it's not so easy as described in the article.</p>\n<!--more-->\n<p>First error I received was </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\">/usr/local/bin/build: line <span class=\"token number\">26</span>: jekyll: <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">command</span> not found</code></pre></div>\n<p>What I had to do was to create a Gemfile with the following:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"ruby\"><pre class=\"language-ruby\"><code class=\"language-ruby\">source <span class=\"token string\">\"https://rubygems.org\"</span>\n gem <span class=\"token string\">'jekyll'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'3.7.2'</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>After creating Gemfile next error was:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\">Deprecation: The <span class=\"token string\">'gems'</span> configuration option has been renamed to <span class=\"token string\">'plugins'</span><span class=\"token builtin class-name\">.</span> Please update your config <span class=\"token function\">file</span> accordingly.</code></pre></div>\n<p>Luckily the description here is self-explanatory. Next one was:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\">jekyll <span class=\"token number\">3.7</span>.2 <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> Error: The jekyll-theme-minimal theme could not be found.</code></pre></div>\n<p>I received this because I chose the theme while setting up page on GitHub. I had to remove the line <code class=\"language-text\">theme: jekyll-theme-minimal</code> from <code class=\"language-text\">_config.yml</code> file.</p>\n<p>Next one was not so easy:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\">jekyll <span class=\"token number\">3.7</span>.2 <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> Error:  <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>/opt/build/repo/_config.yml<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>: did not <span class=\"token function\">find</span> expected key <span class=\"token keyword\">while</span> parsing a block mapping at line <span class=\"token number\">6</span> <span class=\"token function\">column</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Fortunately, the line containing the error was pointed out. It contained <code class=\"language-text\">name: Rob Dy</code> what, for some reason, doesn't work on Netlify but works on GitHub. I tried to change it to <code class=\"language-text\">name: &quot;Rob Dy&quot;</code> and that helped.</p>\n<p>Another error I got was:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\">Dependency Error: Yikes<span class=\"token operator\">!</span> It looks like you don't have jekyll-sitemap or one of its dependencies installed. <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">..</span>.<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>I had no idea how this can be resolved but found somewhere that Gemfile is the one to be changed in such cases. I added the lines to add all the gems/plugins I had in <code class=\"language-text\">_config.yml</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"ruby\"><pre class=\"language-ruby\"><code class=\"language-ruby\">gem <span class=\"token string\">'jekyll-sitemap'</span>\ngem <span class=\"token string\">'jekyll-feed'</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>That's it! After that I received <code class=\"language-text\">Site is live</code> and I was able to see the welcome page</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 949px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/8dff834ddf61f15bada6da501335e1a7/14060/2018-01-31%2022_32_33-Rob%20Dy%20%E2%80%93%20In-free-time%20developer.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 44.16135881104034%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"2018-01-31 22_32_33-Rob Dy – In-free-time developer.png\"\n        title=\"2018-01-31 22_32_33-Rob Dy – In-free-time developer.png\"\n        src=\"/static/8dff834ddf61f15bada6da501335e1a7/14060/2018-01-31%2022_32_33-Rob%20Dy%20%E2%80%93%20In-free-time%20developer.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/8dff834ddf61f15bada6da501335e1a7/1f09d/2018-01-31%2022_32_33-Rob%20Dy%20%E2%80%93%20In-free-time%20developer.png 471w,\n/static/8dff834ddf61f15bada6da501335e1a7/f1901/2018-01-31%2022_32_33-Rob%20Dy%20%E2%80%93%20In-free-time%20developer.png 942w,\n/static/8dff834ddf61f15bada6da501335e1a7/14060/2018-01-31%2022_32_33-Rob%20Dy%20%E2%80%93%20In-free-time%20developer.png 949w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 949px) 100vw, 949px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Just one more thing - to also see drafts on the webpage I had to adjust the settings a bit:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 733px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4b6df16ff8c0fdd9e1b8411745a7aacd/00b70/2018-01-31%2022_34_53-Build%20%26%20deploy%20_%20Settings.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 57.11252653927813%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"2018-01-31 22_34_53-Build &amp; deploy _ Settings.png\"\n        title=\"2018-01-31 22_34_53-Build &amp; deploy _ Settings.png\"\n        src=\"/static/4b6df16ff8c0fdd9e1b8411745a7aacd/00b70/2018-01-31%2022_34_53-Build%20%26%20deploy%20_%20Settings.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4b6df16ff8c0fdd9e1b8411745a7aacd/1f09d/2018-01-31%2022_34_53-Build%20%26%20deploy%20_%20Settings.png 471w,\n/static/4b6df16ff8c0fdd9e1b8411745a7aacd/00b70/2018-01-31%2022_34_53-Build%20%26%20deploy%20_%20Settings.png 733w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 733px) 100vw, 733px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>","frontmatter":{"date":"2018-01-31 10:11","title":"Setup Jekyll blog with Netlify","description":"I'm explaining how to configured Jekyll-based blog to be hosted on Netlify.","tags":["jekyll","netlify"]}}},"pageContext":{"id":"e01c4647-6bba-5d55-9f07-e3eeebf1773d"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2483265550"]}